The U.S. and China have been working together on climate change for the past three years, culminating in the Paris Agreement. They will sign the agreement on April 22nd and take steps to join it as soon as possible this year. They encourage other countries to do the same in order to bring the agreement into force quickly. Both countries are committed to implementing the agreement and working with others to combat climate change. They will also work together on clean energy innovation, the Mission Innovation initiative, and the Clean Energy Ministerial. The U.S. and China will continue to cooperate on climate change through various working groups and centers. They will also take concrete steps to use public resources to finance the transition to low carbon technologies. The joint efforts by China and the U.S. on climate change will be a lasting legacy of their partnership.